column32: 'A dirty or Bad Primary Charge Roller (PCR): this will show on the test print as vertical gray streaks down the page
column33: as a gray background throughout the page
column34: or as ghosting where part of a previously printed area is repeated. A hole in the PCR will leave a mark that repeats every 44mm. If there is a hole
column35: this will eventually burn a hole in the drum
column36: and ruin it.\nDirty PCR Connection: This will show as horizontal dark black bars across the page
column37: or as shading throughout the page.\nScratched Drum: This is shown by a very thin
column38: perfectly straight line that runs from the top to the bottom of the test page.\nChipped Drum: This will show as a dot or series of dots that repeat every 96mm.\nLight Damaged Drum: This will show up as a shaded area on the test print that should be white. Again this will repeat every 96mm.']
